@startuml FE06_ViewFloodMap
title FE06 - View Flood Map (Real-time Water Levels)

actor User
participant UI
participant GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint
participant MediatR
participant GetMapCurrentStatusHandler
participant Repository
database Database

User -> UI: 1. Open flood map view
UI -> GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint: 2. GET /api/map/current-status\n(bounds, status)

alt Validation failed
    GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint --> UI: 3. 400 Bad Request
    UI --> User: 4. Show validation error
else Validation passed
    GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint -> MediatR: 5. Send(GetMapCurrentStatusRequest)
    MediatR -> GetMapCurrentStatusHandler: 6. Handle(request)

    GetMapCurrentStatusHandler -> Repository: 7. Get stations\nwith optional filters
    Repository -> Database: 8. SELECT Stations\nWHERE lat/lng IN bounds\nAND status = ?
    Database --> Repository: 9. List<Station>
    Repository --> GetMapCurrentStatusHandler: 10. List<Station>

    GetMapCurrentStatusHandler -> Repository: 11. Get latest readings\nfor each station
    Repository -> Database: 12. SELECT SensorReadings\nGROUP BY StationId\nORDER BY MeasuredAt DESC
    Database --> Repository: 13. Latest readings
    Repository --> GetMapCurrentStatusHandler: 14. Dictionary<StationId, Reading>

    GetMapCurrentStatusHandler -> GetMapCurrentStatusHandler: 15. Calculate flood severity\nfor each station

    GetMapCurrentStatusHandler -> GetMapCurrentStatusHandler: 16. Build GeoJSON\nFeatureCollection

    alt No stations found
        GetMapCurrentStatusHandler --> MediatR: 17. Response\n(success: false, 404)
        MediatR --> GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint: 18. Response
        GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint --> UI: 19. 404 Not Found
        UI --> User: 20. No stations in area
    else Stations found
        GetMapCurrentStatusHandler --> MediatR: 21. Response\n(success: true, GeoJSON)
        MediatR --> GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint: 22. Response
        GetMapCurrentStatusEndpoint --> UI: 23. 200 OK\n(GeoJSON FeatureCollection)
        UI --> User: 24. Display map with\nreal-time water levels
    end
end

@enduml
